This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object pose estimation from 2D and 3D data. It may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves 3D modeling and representation. Additionally, it may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses a CNN-based framework for pose estimation. The paper also involves manual annotation and fine-grained recognition, which may make it relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, it may be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with image and 3D data.
